A PEDESTRIAN was hit and killed by a train on a level crossing near Heidedal in Bloemfontein on Wednesday, 11 January. Heidedal cops reportedly received a call about a train accident near East-end Industrial Park. “On arrival, members found the dismembered body of a male in his mid 40s. He was wearing a black jersey with white stripes. Heidedal police have opened a case of culpable homicide for further investigation,” said police spokesman Sergeant Mahlomola Kareli. Kareli appealed with pedestrians to be observant while crossing the railway lines. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  “Cross railroad tracks only at designated pedestrian or roadway crossings and obey all warning signs and signals. Always stop, look both ways and listen for trains before crossing the tracks,” said Kareli. Cops are pleading with the community nearby to assist in identifying him. Kareli urged anyone with information to contact Heidedal Police Station commander Lieutenant-Colonel Pule on 071 606 5715.